comment:
* Defines a request object to configure a Wi-Fi Aware network. Built using
 * {@link ConfigRequest.Builder}. Configuration is requested using
 * {@link WifiAwareManager#attach(AttachCallback, android.os.Handler)}.
 * Note that the actual achieved configuration may be different from the
 * requested configuration - since different applications may request different
 * configurations.
 *
 * @hide

variables.name: CLUSTER_ID_MIN
variables.comment: * Lower range of possible cluster ID.

variables.name: CLUSTER_ID_MAX
variables.comment: * Upper range of possible cluster ID.

variables.name: NAN_BAND_24GHZ
variables.comment: * Indices for configuration variables which are specified per band.

variables.name: DW_INTERVAL_NOT_INIT
variables.comment: * Magic values for Discovery Window (DW) interval configuration

variables.name: mSupport5gBand
variables.comment: * Indicates whether 5G band support is requested.

variables.name: mSupport6gBand
variables.comment: * Indicates whether 6G band support is requested.

variables.name: mClusterLow
variables.comment:
* Specifies the desired lower range of the cluster ID. Must be lower then
     * {@link ConfigRequest#mClusterHigh}.

variables.name: mClusterHigh
variables.comment:
* Specifies the desired higher range of the cluster ID. Must be higher then
     * {@link ConfigRequest#mClusterLow}.

variables.name: mDiscoveryWindowInterval
variables.comment: * Specifies the discovery window interval for the device on NAN_BAND_*.

methods.name: public void writeToParcel(Parcel dest, int flags)
public void validate() throws IllegalArgumentException
methods.comment:
* Verifies that the contents of the ConfigRequest are valid. Otherwise
     * throws an IllegalArgumentException.

methodNames: public void writeToParcel(Parcel dest, int flags)
